IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

16:43.306 --> 16:45.091
LOOK,
SHE'S GOING FOR LIEUTENANT.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.484
I HAVE TO WRITE HER
AN APPRAISAL OF PROMOTABILITY

16:47.615 --> 16:50.183
SO SHE'S BUTTERING ME UP,
IT'S STRICTLY BUSINESS.

16:51.445 --> 16:52.924
SO WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO TELL ME
IS THAT YOU DON'T HAVE

16:53.055 --> 16:54.013
ANY FEELINGS AT ALL FOR ALEX?

16:54.143 --> 16:55.492
NONE WHATSOEVER.

16:55.623 --> 16:57.668
ANY RELATIONSHIP I HAVE
WITH ALEX RYKER

16:57.799 --> 16:58.887
IS PURELY PROFESSIONAL.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.846
NOW,
WHAT'S THIS DEAL WITH TOWER 24?

17:01.977 --> 17:02.934
AH, IT'S NOTHING.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.196
NO, NO, NO, I'M YOUR FRIEND.

17:04.327 --> 17:05.633
WHAT'S THIS DEAL WITH TOWER 24?

17:05.762 --> 17:07.765
ALL RIGHT, WELL,

17:08.810 --> 17:10.333
IT'S THE CLOSEST TOWER
TO THE FLORIST SHOP

17:10.464 --> 17:11.638
RIGHT.

17:11.769 --> 17:13.380
I'M GOING TO BUY
TWO DOZEN ROSES, PUT THEM IN

17:13.510 --> 17:16.425
BEFORE SHE OPENS UP, WITH A NOTE
STATING MY INTENTIONS.

17:16.557 --> 17:17.819
AH, THE OLD FASHIONED APPROACH.

17:17.949 --> 17:19.386
WELL, I'M AN OLD FASHIONED GUY.

17:19.516 --> 17:21.083
THEN YOU CASUALLY APPROACH
THE TOWER WHILE SHE'S FEELING

17:21.214 --> 17:22.476
WARM AND GUSHY...

17:22.606 --> 17:24.260
AND HOW COULD SHE SAY NO?

17:24.913 --> 17:25.740
THAT'S THE PLAN.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

17:25.869 --> 17:27.523
NEWMIE, YOU'RE THE MAN.

17:28.176 --> 17:29.091
THANKS.

17:33.008 --> 17:33.965
[SIGHING]

17:34.096 --> 17:35.619
HERE'S YOUR FLAN.

17:37.186 --> 17:38.057
ENJOY.

17:43.236 --> 17:44.280
WELL,
I HEAR THE FOOD'S EXCELLENT.

17:44.411 --> 17:45.673
YEAH, IT'S PRETTY EXPENSIVE.

17:45.803 --> 17:46.674
YEAH, WELL.

17:46.804 --> 17:47.979
-GOOD EVENING.
-GOOD EVENING.

17:48.110 --> 17:49.503
WOULD EITHER OF YOU
CARE FOR A COCKTAIL?

17:49.633 --> 17:53.028
UHM, WELL, YOU KNOW ACTUALLY
I THINK I WOULD LIKE

17:53.159 --> 17:56.858
A GLASS OF WHITE WINE,
SOMETHING DRY IF YOU HAVE IT.

17:56.988 --> 17:58.294
WE HAVE A VERY NICE CHARDONNAY.

17:58.425 --> 17:59.730
THAT SOUNDS PERFECT.

17:59.861 --> 18:00.818
NOTHING FOR ME.

18:00.949 --> 18:02.472
OH, COME ON MITCH,
IT'S MY TREAT.

18:03.169 --> 18:05.084
WELL, THEN I'LL HAVE A BOTTLE
OF MINERAL WATER.

18:05.214 --> 18:06.650
WE HAVE SEVERAL
DIFFERENT BRANDS.

18:06.781 --> 18:10.045
WELL, SINCE IT'S HER TREAT,
I'LL HAVE SOMETHING FRENCH.

18:10.567 --> 18:12.178
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK
WITH YOUR DRINKS.

18:15.659 --> 18:16.530
[SIGHING]

18:17.661 --> 18:19.576
WELL, IT'S REALLY NICE
SEEING YOU OUTSIDE OF WORK.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.057
YOU SEEM DIFFERENT.

18:23.928 --> 18:25.234
DIFFERENT? HOW SO?

18:26.496 --> 18:28.629
MORE RELAXED, MAYBE?

18:29.369 --> 18:31.110
ARE YOU SAYING
I'M TOO TENSE AT WORK?

18:31.240 --> 18:33.460
NO, I'M NOT SAYING THAT AT ALL

18:33.590 --> 18:34.852
AND I DID NOT COME HERE
TO BICKER.

18:34.983 --> 18:35.853
OK.

18:36.985 --> 18:40.728
LOOK,
EVER SINCE I CAME TO BAYWATCH,

18:40.858 --> 18:43.600
I FEEL THAT WE HAVE HAD
THIS ADVERSARIAL RELATIONSHIP.

18:43.731 --> 18:46.516
YEAH, YEAH, I'VE NOTICED THAT.

18:46.647 --> 18:49.389
BUT THE OTHER DAY, THAT CHANGED.

18:49.824 --> 18:51.260
I MEAN, AT LEAST FOR ME IT DID.

18:56.483 --> 19:00.008
YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER REALLY
BOUGHT INTO THE CONCEPT

19:00.139 --> 19:02.402
OF A BONDING EXPERIENCE
BUT I JUST

19:02.532 --> 19:06.014
I FEEL LIKE WE SHARED
SOMETHING SPECIAL

19:07.798 --> 19:10.279
AND IT HAS HAD
A TREMENDOUS IMPACT ON ME.

19:11.454 --> 19:12.499
WHAT HAS?

19:13.282 --> 19:15.589
WHEN WE RESCUED THAT LITTLE
KOREAN GIRL, YOU KNOW?

19:15.719 --> 19:17.939
OH, RIGHT, YEAH.

19:18.069 --> 19:20.768
I FELT THE ADRENALINE FLOWING
AND...

19:25.033 --> 19:26.121
THAT MOMENT, YOU KNOW,

19:26.252 --> 19:28.471
BETWEEN LIFE AND DEATH,
IT JUST...

19:30.604 --> 19:32.562
AND THEN WHEN SHE STARTED
BREATHING AGAIN

19:34.129 --> 19:36.000
IT WAS LIKE THIS MIRACLE,
YOU KNOW?

19:37.350 --> 19:38.481
[LAUGHING]

19:38.612 --> 19:40.309
GOD,
DOES ANY OF THIS MAKE ANY SENSE?

19:40.440 --> 19:43.312
YES, YES, ALL OF IT.

19:43.443 --> 19:45.314
I MEAN, TOTALLY.

19:56.064 --> 19:57.021
[KNOCKING]

20:04.551 --> 20:05.595
-HI.
-HEY.

20:05.726 --> 20:07.118
I HOPE I'M NOT INTERRUPTING
ANYTHING.

20:07.249 --> 20:08.294
NO, COME ON IN.

20:10.034 --> 20:11.558
OH, I CAN ONLY STAY A MINUTE.

20:14.735 --> 20:15.779
WHAT'S UP?

20:16.867 --> 20:19.218
I JUST WANTED TO TELL YOU
THAT MY BOSS LOVED YOU

20:19.348 --> 20:22.830
AND SHE WANTS YOU TO BE
THE OFFICIAL SPOKESMAN

20:22.960 --> 20:25.006
FOR OUR ENTIRE LINE OF PRODUCTS.

20:25.136 --> 20:26.964
CODY, WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
A SIX FIGURE

20:27.095 --> 20:29.228
PERSONAL SERVICES CONTRACT!

20:29.358 --> 20:30.403
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

20:30.533 --> 20:33.101
NO, SHE SEES YOU
AS A POTENTIAL SUPERSTAR!

20:34.885 --> 20:37.758
YES! WHOO!

20:38.628 --> 20:39.586
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS!

20:40.239 --> 20:41.805
WHAT,
THAT YOUR DREAM IS COMING TRUE?

20:41.936 --> 20:42.893
YEAH!

20:43.024 --> 20:44.460
FEELS GOOD, DOESN'T IT?

20:44.591 --> 20:45.418
SURE DOES.

20:48.551 --> 20:50.640
NONE OF THIS WOULD HAVE BEEN
POSSIBLE WITHOUT YOU.

20:51.685 --> 20:53.817
OH, THAT'S NICE OF YOU TO SAY.

20:53.948 --> 20:54.905
NO, I MEAN IT.

20:58.431 --> 21:01.825
AND SOMEDAY,
YOU'LL GET TO THANK ME

21:02.652 --> 21:04.654
BUT NOT
WHILE YOU'RE IN TRAINING.

21:05.916 --> 21:07.091
YOU NEED TO STAY FOCUSED.

21:07.875 --> 21:10.399
YOU HAVE A LOT OF HARD
WORK AHEAD OF YOU, OK?

21:12.445 --> 21:13.272
GOOD NIGHT.

21:14.969 --> 21:15.883
HEY, WAIT A SECOND!

21:17.667 --> 21:19.278
WHEN DO WE SIGN THE CONTRACT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT?

21:19.408 --> 21:21.671
AS SOON AS YOU QUALIFY
FOR THE OLYMPIC TRIALS.

21:22.933 --> 21:24.935
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE POOL
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

21:35.250 --> 21:36.599
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
THE DESSERT CART?

21:36.730 --> 21:37.774
-OH YEAH, THAT'S FANTASTIC--
-NO, I DON'T THINK--

21:37.905 --> 21:39.341
I COULD EAT ANOTHER BITE.

21:39.472 --> 21:41.343
I'LL GIVE YOU A MOMENT
TO DECIDE.

21:41.474 --> 21:42.257
THANK YOU.

21:42.388 --> 21:43.258
THANK YOU.

21:46.740 --> 21:49.525
TO A MAN
WHO NEVER CEASES TO AMAZE ME.

21:49.656 --> 21:52.354
TO THE WOMAN WHO KNOWS
HOW TO GET WHAT SHE WANTS.

21:55.052 --> 21:56.271
WHAT DID YOU MEAN BY THAT?

21:56.402 --> 21:59.361
ALEX, YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO GO TO
ALL THIS TROUBLE.

21:59.492 --> 22:02.016
ALTHOUGH I MUST ADMIT,
THE FOOD WAS DELICIOUS.

22:02.973 --> 22:04.410
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:04.540 --> 22:06.325
ABOUT BECOMING A LIEUTENANT.

22:07.413 --> 22:09.763
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GROVEL
ANY MORE.

22:09.893 --> 22:11.286
THE JOB IS YOURS!

22:12.940 --> 22:14.245
GROVEL?

22:15.246 --> 22:17.466
I AM SITTING HERE POURING
MY HEART OUT TO YOU

22:17.597 --> 22:20.208
AND YOU THINK
I'M SUCKING UP FOR A PROMOTION?

22:20.339 --> 22:21.644
-I DIDN'T SAY THAT.
-YES, YOU DID.

22:21.775 --> 22:23.429
-I DIDN'T MEAN IT.
-YES, YOU DID.

22:23.559 --> 22:24.908
I SAID IT, BUT I DIDN'T MEAN IT.

22:25.039 --> 22:26.780
YOU KNOW WHAT, DON'T SAY
ANOTHER WORD. JUST TAKE ME HOME.

22:26.910 --> 22:28.390
I'M SORRY, I...

22:29.391 --> 22:30.392
EXCUSE ME.

22:30.523 --> 22:31.437
NO DESSERT?

22:31.567 --> 22:32.568
I WOULD JUST LIKE
THE CHECK PLEASE.

22:32.699 --> 22:33.656
-RIGHT AWAY.
-YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY HERE,

22:33.787 --> 22:35.049
-I WILL PAY YOU NOW.
-ALEX, COME ON--

22:35.179 --> 22:37.051
DON'T TOUCH ME!

22:38.574 --> 22:39.923
SHE GAVE ME NINE DOLLARS.

22:40.054 --> 22:43.144
THE BILL COMES
TO $47.26 PLUS TIP.

22:43.840 --> 22:45.102
[PLATES CRASHING]

22:45.233 --> 22:46.626
EXCUSE ME.

22:46.974 --> 22:48.192
PLUS THE DESSERT CART.

22:50.456 --> 22:52.283
[MITCH SIGHING]

22:57.114 --> 22:59.595
[CARS HONKING]

23:09.300 --> 23:10.911
WHAT IS WITH ALL THIS TRAFFIC?

23:12.260 --> 23:13.914
MUST BE AN ACCIDENT.

23:16.743 --> 23:18.397
AND IN MALIBU, ROCK SLIDES HAVE

23:18.527 --> 23:21.095
COMPLETELY SHUT DOWN
PACIFIC COAST HIGHWAY

23:21.225 --> 23:22.662
BETWEEN MALIBU PIER
AND SANTA MONICA CANYON.

23:22.792 --> 23:23.750
OH, NO.

23:24.403 --> 23:26.230
CALTRANS
ESTIMATES THAT THE CLOSURE

23:26.361 --> 23:27.884
WILL REMAIN IN EFFECT
UNTIL MORNING.

23:28.015 --> 23:29.364
MORNING!?

23:29.495 --> 23:32.846
ONCE AGAIN, PCH SHUT DOWN
IN BOTH DIRECTIONS.

23:32.976 --> 23:34.064
[LAUGHING]

23:34.195 --> 23:36.327
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME
WE'RE STUCK HERE.

23:36.458 --> 23:38.591
WELL, THIS IS TURNING
INTO QUITE AN EVENING.

23:38.721 --> 23:40.549
I AM NOT SPENDING MY EVENING
LIKE THIS.

23:40.680 --> 23:41.855
I AM GOING TO WALK HOME.

23:41.985 --> 23:43.204
TEN MILES IN THE DARK?

23:43.334 --> 23:44.640
I WILL STAY ALONG THE BEACH.

23:44.771 --> 23:47.034
AT HIGH TIDE? YOU'LL NEVER
MAKE IT PAST TOPANGA.

23:47.948 --> 23:51.038
FACE FACTS ALEX, WE'RE SPENDING
THE NIGHT TOGETHER.

23:52.256 --> 23:53.562
OH DEAR GOD.

23:53.693 --> 23:56.260
I'M NOT EXACTLY THRILLED
AT THE PROPOSITION EITHER.

23:57.566 --> 24:02.266
I GUESS THIS IS WHAT YOU
CALL A DE-BONDING EXPERIENCE.

24:02.397 --> 24:04.878
NO, THIS IS WHAT I WOULD CALL
A NIGHTMARE.

24:06.183 --> 24:09.099
LOOK, I DO NOT HAVE
THE ENERGY TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

24:09.230 --> 24:10.840
I JUST WANT TO GET SOME REST,
OK?

24:12.755 --> 24:13.843
DO THESE SEATS GO BACK?

24:14.583 --> 24:15.454
NO.

24:18.282 --> 24:20.415
JEEZ, WILL YOU LOOK
AT ALL THE JUNK BACK HERE?

24:23.418 --> 24:24.854
WHERE ARE WE SUPPOSED TO SLEEP?

24:32.079 --> 24:34.429
WELCOME TO TOWER SUITE
NUMBER 24.

24:35.996 --> 24:37.214
GREAT.

24:37.345 --> 24:40.522
WELL, THIS COULD BE COZY.

24:41.871 --> 24:43.307
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE STILL ANGRY.

24:43.438 --> 24:44.831
YOU KNOW WHAT, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE SO INSENSITIVE.

24:44.961 --> 24:46.006
I SAID I WAS SORRY!

24:46.136 --> 24:48.138
WELL,
I DON'T ACCEPT YOUR APOLOGY.

24:49.096 --> 24:51.881
THERE HAS GOT TO BE
A FLASHLIGHT HERE SOMEWHERE.

24:52.012 --> 24:54.536
IN THE CABINET,
FOR THE LAST 20 YEARS.

24:59.019 --> 25:00.194
AH, GOD!

25:01.456 --> 25:03.458
YOU ARE HAVING
A HORRIBLE NIGHT.

25:03.589 --> 25:05.504
YOU KNOW, YOU ARE SO NOT FUNNY.

25:05.634 --> 25:07.114
OH COME ON, RYKER,
WILL YOU LIGHTEN UP?

25:07.244 --> 25:09.899
I MEAN, FOR GOD'S SAKES,
DON'T YOU FIND IT A LITTLE BIT

25:10.030 --> 25:13.337
IRONIC THAT WE'RE HERE
IN THIS TOWER ALONE TOGETHER?

25:13.990 --> 25:15.731
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS?

25:15.862 --> 25:17.951
NO, BUT I GOT A FEELING
YOU'RE GOING TO TELL ME.

25:18.081 --> 25:20.867
YOU HAVE NO CLUE
WHEN IT COMES TO WOMEN.

25:22.564 --> 25:25.698
ALL RIGHT, BLANKET OR PILLOW?

25:27.351 --> 25:29.876
BLANKET. THANK YOU.

25:31.051 --> 25:32.226
I AM GOING TO SLEEP NOW.

25:32.922 --> 25:33.836
GOOD.

25:33.967 --> 25:34.968
-GOOD NIGHT.
-GOOD NIGHT.

25:42.584 --> 25:45.326
WOULD YOU MIND TURNING
YOUR FLASHLIGHT OFF PLEASE?

25:45.456 --> 25:46.457
AS SOON AS I UNDRESS.

25:46.588 --> 25:48.982
EXCUSE ME?

25:49.112 --> 25:50.984
I'M ONLY KIDDING, IT'S A JOKE!

25:51.114 --> 25:52.420
GOD, WILL YOU RELAX?

25:52.551 --> 25:54.204
WHAT DO YOU THINK
IS GOING TO HAPPEN HERE?

25:55.031 --> 25:55.945
NOTHING.

25:56.076 --> 25:58.426
OK, SO CHILL OUT.

26:05.781 --> 26:07.217
OH, MAN.

26:09.089 --> 26:10.569
[SIGHING]

26:10.699 --> 26:11.613
GOD!

26:11.744 --> 26:13.006
WHAT IS THE MATTER?

26:13.136 --> 26:15.312
I HAVE GOT A SPASM IN MY NECK.

26:15.443 --> 26:17.140
[SIGHING]

26:18.315 --> 26:19.403
WANT A PILLOW?

26:20.883 --> 26:21.710
YES.

26:23.233 --> 26:24.800
AH, GIVE ME THE BLANKET.

26:25.714 --> 26:27.498
YOU KNOW, YOU JUST...

26:29.762 --> 26:33.504
OH, THANK YOU.
THAT IS MUCH, MUCH BETTER.

26:37.639 --> 26:38.771
BRR.

26:41.251 --> 26:42.122
BRR.

26:43.123 --> 26:44.428
MM?

26:44.559 --> 26:45.995
I SAID "BRR".

26:46.126 --> 26:49.085
OH, DON'T EVEN THINK IT.

26:49.216 --> 26:51.958
YOU KNOW WHAT, THE BLANKET
DOESN'T EVEN HALFWAY COVER YOU.

26:52.088 --> 26:53.176
ANYBODY EVER TELL
YOU YOU'RE LIKE

26:53.307 --> 26:54.264
AN INCREDIBLY DEMANDING WIFE?

26:54.395 --> 26:55.526
