CAREFUL OUT THERE, LADIES.

32:43.004 --> 32:44.223
OK. THANKS!

32:55.843 --> 32:57.323
HEY, STOP IT!

33:01.327 --> 33:03.416
[PHONE RINGING]

33:04.939 --> 33:06.506
TOWER 8, THIS IS MADISON.

33:06.810 --> 33:08.508
HEY, CODY, HOW YOU DOING?
IT'S ALEX.

33:08.638 --> 33:09.770
EH, IT'S PRETTY QUIET.

33:09.900 --> 33:11.380
NOT MANY PEOPLE IN THE WATER.

33:11.511 --> 33:13.252
WELL, THAT'S A GOOD THING
CAUSE THE SURF'S PRETTY TRICKY.

33:13.861 --> 33:18.344
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I CAN SEE
A RIP BOILING RIGHT NOW.

33:18.474 --> 33:20.085
ALL RIGHT, COOL.
HEY, THANKS FOR THE HEADS UP.

33:20.215 --> 33:21.434
YEAH, ANY TIME.

33:25.090 --> 33:26.134
NEWMIE--

33:26.265 --> 33:27.353
I TOLD YOU,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO EXPLAIN.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.529
PCH WAS SHUT DOWN.

33:29.659 --> 33:32.053
WE WERE STRANDED,
THERE WAS NO PLACE TO SLEEP.

33:32.184 --> 33:33.663
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
THOSE ROSES COST ME?

33:33.794 --> 33:35.578
-NOTHING HAPPENED, I SWEAR.
-UH-HUH.

33:50.637 --> 33:54.423
[GASPING]

33:59.950 --> 34:03.128
HELP! HELP, I'M OVER HERE!

34:05.260 --> 34:06.522
HEY!

34:06.653 --> 34:08.524
HELP ME!

34:14.530 --> 34:15.792
I SWEAR TO YOU, NOTHING--

34:15.922 --> 34:17.489
IF YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,
ASK ALEX, OK?

34:17.620 --> 34:19.621
AMF 201 295.

34:19.753 --> 34:21.014
YES, 295, COME BACK.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.973
LIFEGUARD IN THE WATER, TOWER 8.

34:23.103 --> 34:24.366
WE'RE ON IT. HOP ON!

34:27.152 --> 34:29.023
[SIREN WAILING]

34:32.244 --> 34:33.592
[WOMAN GASPING]

34:33.723 --> 34:34.594
HERE!

34:42.254 --> 34:43.559
ARE YOU OK?

34:43.690 --> 34:44.821
I'M OK BUT PLEASE,
MY FRIEND OVER THERE, HELP HER!

34:44.952 --> 34:46.040
HELP ME!

34:46.170 --> 34:47.520
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

34:48.216 --> 34:49.087
HOLD THIS.

34:49.652 --> 34:50.958
HOLD THAT, ALL RIGHT?

35:02.970 --> 35:04.711
YEAH, IS THERE A RESCUE BOAT
IN THE VICINITY?

35:05.277 --> 35:07.279
TELL THEM IT'S CODE R,
I'M LEAVING MY TOWER NOW.

35:12.022 --> 35:12.936
OVER HERE!

35:21.510 --> 35:23.425
TAKE MY HAND. TAKE MY HAND.

35:24.600 --> 35:27.342
IT'S OK, I GOT YOU.

35:32.652 --> 35:34.088
ARE YOU OK?

35:35.698 --> 35:37.613
[SIREN WAILING]

35:37.744 --> 35:38.832
OCEAN LIFEGUARD

35:38.962 --> 35:40.747
-CODY CAN'T GET HER OUT.
-WHY NOT?

35:40.877 --> 35:43.184
SOMETHING'S WRONG.
I GOT A RESCUE BOAT ON THE WAY.

35:43.315 --> 35:45.055
ALL RIGHT, YOU WATCH HIS WATER,
WE'RE ON IT.

35:45.186 --> 35:46.187
ALL RIGHT.

35:47.971 --> 35:49.103
PLEASE HELP!

36:16.435 --> 36:19.786
[DISTORTED AUDIO]

36:20.700 --> 36:22.397
SOMETHING'S WRONG.

36:22.528 --> 36:24.182
IT'S GOING TO BE OK.

36:25.444 --> 36:26.532
SOMEONE'S GOING TO HELP US.

36:29.752 --> 36:30.753
IT'S GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

36:31.580 --> 36:32.494
FREEZING.

36:45.681 --> 36:46.943
HERE, HOLD ON TO THE CAN.

36:47.074 --> 36:48.815
LIFEGUARD BAYWATCH

36:51.818 --> 36:52.775
HANG ON, OK?

36:52.906 --> 36:53.994
I'M FREEZING.

37:02.002 --> 37:03.699
HERE, GRAB THE CAN.

37:04.439 --> 37:05.310
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

37:05.440 --> 37:06.354
I DON'T KNOW.

37:08.051 --> 37:09.270
HOLD THE CAN.

37:14.928 --> 37:16.408
ALL RIGHT, TAKE IT EASY.

37:16.538 --> 37:18.279
EASY. ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

37:32.902 --> 37:34.208
OK, I'VE GOT YOU.

37:35.557 --> 37:36.993
GET A BLANKET ON HER, RIGHT NOW.

37:37.124 --> 37:38.256
GOT IT.

37:38.386 --> 37:39.866
LET'S GET HIM ON BOARD,
HE'S OUT OF IT.

37:39.996 --> 37:41.128
WHERE'S NEWMIE?

37:41.433 --> 37:42.651
HE'S TRYING TO GO TO SHORE.

37:42.782 --> 37:44.262
GET A BLANKET IN HERE, COME ON!

37:45.045 --> 37:46.002
WHAT HAPPENED?

37:46.133 --> 37:47.308
WHEN HE GOT TO ME
HE WAS SHAKING,

37:47.439 --> 37:48.657
LIKE HE WAS REALLY COLD

37:48.788 --> 37:50.137
AND THEN HE WENT INTO SHOCK.

37:50.920 --> 37:52.487
LET'S GO, HE'S HYPOTHERMIC!

37:53.923 --> 37:54.968
I'LL GET YOU WARM.

38:02.584 --> 38:04.673
HEY, THAT'S ENOUGH WATER.

38:04.804 --> 38:06.066
GET IN THE SAUNA AND DRY OFF.

38:07.285 --> 38:08.808
YEAH, THAT'S WHERE I'M HEADED.

38:08.938 --> 38:09.809
YOUR TEMPERATURE'S NOT UP.

38:09.939 --> 38:11.114
I'M TAKING YOU IN
FOR OBSERVATION.

38:11.245 --> 38:13.682
NO MAN, NO HOSPITALS. I'M FINE.

38:14.553 --> 38:16.511
I TALKED TO LIZ
AND I TOLD HER WHAT HAPPENED.

38:16.990 --> 38:19.035
YEAH, LISTEN MAN,
DON'T BLAME HER.

38:19.166 --> 38:20.776
I'M THE ONE WHO SCREWED UP HERE.

38:23.083 --> 38:25.041
I'M NOT GOING TO STAND HERE
AND LECTURE YOU

38:25.172 --> 38:26.608
ON WHAT YOU'RE DOING
TO YOUR BODY.

38:27.130 --> 38:29.350
THAT'S YOUR BUSINESS
AND THAT'S NOT WHAT CONCERNS ME.

38:29.785 --> 38:30.699
WHAT DOES?

38:30.830 --> 38:32.179
YOUR ABILITIES AS A LIFE GUARD.

38:32.875 --> 38:34.399
LOOK, YOU GOTTA MAKE
A CHOICE HERE, PAL.

38:34.529 --> 38:37.140
YOU CAN NOT BE AN OCEAN
LIFEGUARD AND HAVE 2% BODY FAT.

38:37.271 --> 38:39.142
MITCH, THE ONLY WAY
I CAN MAKE THE OLYMPICS

38:39.273 --> 38:40.318
IS TO STAY ON THIS DIET.

38:40.448 --> 38:41.449
YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

38:41.580 --> 38:43.016
THE NUMBERS DON'T LIE.

38:43.146 --> 38:45.061
I'M SWIMMING FASTER THAN I EVER
HAVE IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

38:46.280 --> 38:47.194
WHAT ELSE COULD IT BE?

38:47.325 --> 38:48.413
IF THAT'S HOW YOU FEEL,

38:48.543 --> 38:49.892
THEN YOU'VE GOT
A MAJOR DECISION TO MAKE.

38:54.854 --> 38:57.335
IF YOU WERE ME,
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

38:59.685 --> 39:00.642
TOUGH CALL.

39:01.426 --> 39:03.558
ON ONE HAND, YOU'RE
THE BEST LIFEGUARD TO COME

39:03.689 --> 39:04.516
BY BAYWATCH
IN THE LAST TEN YEARS.

39:05.604 --> 39:08.781
ON THE OTHER, I HAVE BEEN
LOOKING FOR AN EXCUSE

39:08.911 --> 39:09.999
TO GO TO SYDNEY NEXT YEAR.

39:20.009 --> 39:22.316
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS

39:23.056 --> 39:23.839
HEY, MITCH.

39:23.970 --> 39:24.884
HEY!

39:25.145 --> 39:26.407
-YOU GOING TO WORK OUT?
-YUP.

39:26.538 --> 39:28.627
HEY, MIND IF I WALK ALONG
FOR A MINUTE?

39:28.757 --> 39:29.628
SURE.

39:30.629 --> 39:32.195
HEY, WHAT WAS GOING ON
WITH NEWMIE THIS MORNING?

39:32.326 --> 39:33.153
WHAT WAS HE SO UPSET ABOUT?

39:33.283 --> 39:34.241
WHAT WAS WITH ALL THOSE ROSES?

39:34.372 --> 39:36.156
UH, THAT'S A LONG STORY

39:36.286 --> 39:37.940
AND I THINK HE SHOULD TELL YOU
HIMSELF.

39:38.941 --> 39:40.465
OK.

39:40.595 --> 39:42.902
LISTEN, I WAS THINKING ABOUT
SOMETHING YOU SAID LAST NIGHT.

39:43.032 --> 39:44.425
WHAT'S THAT?

39:44.556 --> 39:46.427
WELL, YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT ME
BECOMING LIEUTENANT

39:46.558 --> 39:47.950
AND YOU SAID THAT I COULD.

39:48.081 --> 39:49.691
I SAID THE JOB IS YOURS.

39:50.300 --> 39:51.389
DOES THAT OFFER STILL STAND?

39:52.955 --> 39:54.000
ABSOLUTELY.

39:54.130 --> 39:55.044
GOOD, I ACCEPT.

39:55.958 --> 39:58.787
HAVE YOU WRITTEN THE APPRAISAL
OF PROMOTABILITY YET?

39:58.918 --> 39:59.701
STILL WORKING ON IT.

39:59.832 --> 40:01.399
-CAN I SEE IT?
-NOPE.

40:01.921 --> 40:03.575
COME ON, LOOK, IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M GOING TO REWRITE YOU.

40:03.705 --> 40:05.315
I WON'T CHANGE A SINGLE WORD,
I PROMISE.

40:05.446 --> 40:06.534
SPEAKING OF CHANGE,

40:06.665 --> 40:09.407
YOU OWE ME $47.13 FOR DINNER
LAST NIGHT.

40:09.537 --> 40:10.320
WHAT?

40:10.451 --> 40:11.931
PLUS $25 FOR THE DESSERT CART.

40:12.540 --> 40:13.672
OH COME ON,
THAT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

40:13.802 --> 40:14.847
THEY CAN'T CHARGE ME FOR THAT.

40:14.977 --> 40:16.239
THEY DIDN'T CHARGE YOU,
THEY CHARGED ME.

40:17.327 --> 40:18.677
YOU KNOW, THAT IS RIDICULOUS.

40:18.807 --> 40:19.808
I'M GOING TO CALL THE MANAGER.

40:19.939 --> 40:21.027
YOU STILL GOT THAT RECEIPT?

40:21.157 --> 40:22.289
YEAH, BUT I ALREADY TALKED
TO THE MANAGER

40:22.420 --> 40:23.812
AND THEY WANT 25 BUCKS
FOR THE CART.

40:23.943 --> 40:25.161
WELL, I'M NOT GONNA PAY IT.

40:25.292 --> 40:27.250
ALEX, YOU KNOCKED THE CART OVER.

40:27.381 --> 40:29.992
YOU KNOW WHAT, IT WAS
BECAUSE YOU MADE ME SO MAD.

40:30.123 --> 40:31.429
YEAH, BUT I DIDN'T START
THE WHOLE THING.

40:31.559 --> 40:32.430
YOU STARTED IT.

40:36.869 --> 40:38.697
I'LL BE BACK IN THREE WEEKS,
RIGHT AFTER THE NATIONALS.

40:38.827 --> 40:39.611
GOOD LUCK.

40:39.741 --> 40:40.612
THANKS, MITCH.

40:40.742 --> 40:41.743
YOU CAN DO IT!

40:41.874 --> 40:43.832
EH, WHATEVER HAPPENS HAPPENS.

40:44.616 --> 40:45.921
HEY,
JUST DON'T GIVE AWAY MY LOCKER!

40:46.052 --> 40:47.575
NOT A CHANCE.

40:47.706 --> 40:48.663
WHOO!

40:48.794 --> 40:49.751
[LAUGHING]

40:52.275 --> 40:53.799
SO, CODY TAKE OFF, HUH?

40:53.929 --> 40:55.278
YUP, HE'S ON HIS WAY.

40:55.888 --> 40:56.802
YOU GOTTA ADMIRE THE GUY.

40:57.716 --> 41:00.501
LET'S MAKE A DEAL
HE MAKES THE TEAM,

41:00.632 --> 41:02.068
WE FLY TO SYDNEY
AND WATCH HIM SWIM.

41:02.198 --> 41:03.069
YOU'RE ON, BUDDY.

41:03.765 --> 41:04.766
YOU KNOW, NEWMIE,
I'VE BEEN MEANING

41:04.897 --> 41:05.767
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT SOMETHING.

41:06.464 --> 41:07.900
I MAY HAVE JUMPED THE GUN
THE OTHER DAY

41:08.030 --> 41:09.815
WHEN I SAID I WASN'T INTERESTED
IN ALEX.

41:09.945 --> 41:11.643
OH,
SO YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ALEX?

41:11.773 --> 41:13.993
WELL, IT'S POSSIBLE
THAT I MIGHT BE INTERESTED

41:14.123 --> 41:15.821
AND I WANTED TO MAKE SURE
THAT'S COOL WITH YOU.

41:16.604 --> 41:17.910
HAVE YOU DISCUSSED THIS
WITH ALEX?

41:18.040 --> 41:19.651
NO, BECAUSE I WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU ABOUT IT FIRST.

41:20.608 --> 41:23.089
WELL YOU KNOW SOMETHING MITCH,
I APPRECIATE THAT

41:23.219 --> 41:24.438
BUT I CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

41:24.569 --> 41:25.395
WHY NOT?

41:25.526 --> 41:26.614
HEY, NEWMIE!

41:27.136 --> 41:28.834
HANG ON, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

41:31.140 --> 41:32.664
ALEX AND I ARE GOING SURFING.

41:32.794 --> 41:33.839
WHAT?

41:33.969 --> 41:35.057
[LAUGHING]

41:35.188 --> 41:36.319
COWABUNGA, DUDE!

41:43.413 --> 41:47.413
[ENDING MUSIC]
